Tuesday August 27th 2013 11:36 am -04:00,As Etienne said the idea is function reuse. When someone define a function that does some job don´t repeat that code in some other place just call the function. In this case they provide two functions count_vowels and count_consonants. Using this two functions you must write one statements that returns the number of letters of the word.Apparently in this case using the functions provided or the built-in function len seems to be the same but in another scenario for example count_letters_in_a_var_name it could be not the same.If you want to count letters in this case the function len could not be appropiated try this:>>> len(ab4t5)Check the response and compare with the number of letters in the word (just 3). This is a valid variable name but has 3 letters and 2 numbers. While len will tell you that theres 5 letters using count_vowels and count_consonants will take you to the correct answer.I hope that this helps., Unresolved,11
