Tuesday September 24th 2013 11:45 am -04:00,Any object can be tested for truth value. There are some special values that are considered False and all the rest are considered True.See this link to check all the cases that are evaluated as False: http://docs.python.org/3.2/library/stdtypes.html#truth-value-testingWhen you are going through the lines of a file the variable always have a value that evaluates to True. When the EOF (end of file) is reached the method readline returns an empty string () and this is one of the cases that evaluates to False.Thats why While line:works. line is always evaluated as true until the EOF.I hope it was clear., Resolved,4
